{
  "texts": [
    "For smaller shot sizes (≤ 50 shots), standard deviation was low (∼ 2.5%) decreasing to less than 1% for larger sizes.",
    "We observed this for gbert and medbertde with no impact of different pretraining methods.",
    "We investigate the impact of shot size on the accuracy of predicting the selected primary section classes (Fig. 6a).",
    "Across shot sizes 20-50, the F1-scores of both classes increase in average by 9.2% pp.",
    "Anamnese, with a lower F1-score, benefits more from larger few-shot sizes."
  ]
}